---

# Color System

Colors communicate meaning.

Never decorate.

Never use color because it "looks nice."

Every color has a purpose.

---

# Brand Personality

The visual language should feel

Professional

Trustworthy

Academic

Premium

Editorial

Modern

Minimal

Calm

Confident

Never create

Neon interfaces

Gaming interfaces

Social media interfaces

Overly saturated interfaces

---

# Color Hierarchy

Primitive Colors

↓

Semantic Colors

↓

Component Colors

↓

Feature Colors

Never bypass the hierarchy.

---

# Primitive Colors

Primitive colors represent raw values.

Examples

Blue 50

Blue 100

Blue 200

...

Gray 50

Gray 100

Gray 900

Success Green

Warning Amber

Error Red

Primitive colors should never be consumed directly.

---

# Semantic Colors

Semantic colors describe intent.

Examples

color.background.primary

color.background.secondary

color.surface.primary

color.surface.secondary

color.surface.elevated

color.surface.inverse

color.text.primary

color.text.secondary

color.text.tertiary

color.text.inverse

color.action.primary

color.action.secondary

color.action.disabled

color.border.default

color.border.focus

color.border.error

color.success

color.warning

color.error

color.info

color.overlay

color.shadow

Widgets consume Semantic Colors.

---

# Surface Levels

Support multiple surface elevations.

Examples

surface.level0

surface.level1

surface.level2

surface.level3

surface.level4

Higher surfaces should have subtle contrast.

Never rely on heavy shadows.

---

# Background Layers

Support

App Background

Screen Background

Section Background

Card Background

Modal Background

Overlay Background

Every layer must be distinguishable.

---

# Text Hierarchy

Primary Text

Highest emphasis.

Secondary Text

Supporting information.

Tertiary Text

Metadata.

Disabled Text

Unavailable actions.

Inverse Text

Dark backgrounds.

Never invent additional text colors.

---

# Action Colors

Actions communicate intent.

Primary

Secondary

Destructive

Success

Disabled

Loading

Avoid unnecessary variants.

---

# Feedback Colors

Feedback should always be consistent.

Success

Warning

Error

Information

Neutral

Never invent custom alert colors.

---

# Border Colors

Support

Default

Focused

Hovered

Pressed

Selected

Disabled

Error

Success

---

# Selection Colors

Support

Text Selection

Checkbox

Radio

Switch

Chip

Quiz Option

Flashcard

AI Citation

---

# Component Colors

Every reusable component owns its own semantic mapping.

Example

Primary Button

↓

button.primary.background

↓

color.action.primary

↓

primitive.blue600

The component never references primitive colors.

---

# AI Colors

AI interactions have dedicated semantic colors.

Examples

assistant.background

assistant.border

assistant.text

assistant.citation

assistant.reasoning

assistant.confidence

assistant.streaming

user.background

user.text

system.background

Never reuse chat colors from messaging apps.

AI should feel professional.

---

# Quiz Colors

Quiz colors belong to Quiz.

Examples

quiz.correct

quiz.incorrect

quiz.unanswered

quiz.selected

quiz.review

quiz.flagged

---

# Flashcard Colors

Support

Front

Back

Reveal

Hint

Bookmark

Review

---

# Diagnostic Colors

Support

Excellent

Good

Average

Weak

Critical

Never expose numeric meaning through color alone.

Always combine with text.

---

# Progress Colors

Support

Current

Completed

Locked

In Progress

Pending

Streak

Milestone

---

# Accessibility

Every color combination must satisfy WCAG AA.

Never rely solely on color.

Always support icons or labels.

---

# Dark Theme

Dark Mode should not simply invert colors.

Dark Mode has its own semantic palette.

Reduce glare.

Increase readability.

Preserve hierarchy.

---

# Future Themes

The color system must support

Institution branding

White-label deployments

Seasonal branding

Accessibility themes

without changing widgets.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Never use Color().

Never use hex values.

Never reference primitive colors.

Always consume semantic color tokens.

Every widget must remain brand-independent.